   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First, we fit exploratory k-means models on raw regression outputs with different numbers of clusters. The best solution from both elbow plot and silhouette values appears to be the 2-cluster one. 8-cluster solution also looks the same mathematically, but interpretiation-wise, having a couple extremely small clusters (3-sites cluster, 4-sites clustes, etc.) likely means that outliers got attached to each other again. Either way, the silhouette widths of 0.201 and 0.201 are both quite small, borderline unsatisfactory. For this reason, we attempted to perform k-means on the less noisy first 5 principal components: as per the PCA section, they retain around 82% of the variance.   "
   ]
