  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f0779538-b283-41e5-9155-741282f0e170",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "From the plot on the PC1 and PC2 we can see that the structure is not ideal with cluster 1 being the smallest and very spread out on the second component, and clusters 2 anf 3 being very spread out on the first component. Of course, the clustering was performed on all 5 components, not just the 2 visible on the plot. It is worth mentioning, however, that paired with modest silhouette values, it says that the data did not get exceptionally sharply or cleanly separated.\n",
    "\n",
    "Note: GMM was also attempted along with k-means but we decided against including it, because while its best (k=2) solution yielded very similar silhouette width as the best k-means solution (k=3) and had normal-sized clusters, they were not suitable for meaningful interpretation, their separation logic was not logically clear. For this reason as well, we decided to stick with k-means as the main algorithm. "
   ]
